  "name": "ZLEMA KVO Trend Strength Trader",
  "description": "This algorithm employs a combination of the Zero-Lag Exponential Moving Average (ZLEMA) and the Klinger Volume Oscillator (KVO) to identify and capitalize on trend-following opportunities. It initiates long positions based on specific crossover conditions, ensuring that trades are supported by volume-driven trend strength.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Create an expert-level TrendFollowing trading algorithm in Python that combines the Zero-Lag Exponential Moving Average (ZLEMA) with the Klinger Volume Oscillator (KVO) on a 15-minute timeframe. Entry Condition: initiate a long position when the 15-min close price crosses above the ZLEMA(21) and KVO(34,55) turns positive from negative, confirming increasing volume-driven trend strength. Exit Condition: close the long trade when price closes below ZLEMA(21) or KVO turns negative. Include a trailing stop based on 1.5 times the Average True Range (ATR) over 14 periods to protect profits. The algorithm should filter out trades during sideways markets by only taking signals when the Average Directional Movement Index (ADX) over 14 periods is above 25.",
